<collectingCountry id="45DD19D4FFF7AF55A49562B4FD7BFE69" box="[165,268,410,436]" name="Thailand" pageId="4" pageNumber="236">Thailand</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="595B24B5FFF7AF55A52762B4FE25FE69" author="Phukhamsakda, C. &amp; McKenzie, E. H. C. &amp; Phillips, A. J. L. &amp; Gareth Jones, E. B. &amp; Jayarama Bhat, D. &amp; Stadler, M. &amp; Bhunjun, C. S. &amp; Wanasinghe, D. N. &amp; Thongbai, B. &amp; Camporesi, E. &amp; Jayawardena, R. S. &amp; Perera, R. H. &amp; Ekanayake, A. H. &amp; Tibpromma, S. &amp; Doilom, M. &amp; Xu, J. &amp; Hyde, K. D." box="[279,594,410,436]" pageId="4" pageNumber="236" pagination="1 - 203" refId="ref7537" refString="Phukhamsakda, C., McKenzie, E. H. C., Phillips, A. J. L., Gareth Jones, E. B., Jayarama Bhat, D., Stadler, M., Bhunjun, C. S., Wanasinghe, D. N., Thongbai, B., Camporesi, E., Ertz, D., Jayawardena, R. S., Perera, R. H., Ekanayake, A. H., Tibpromma, S., Doilom, M., Xu, J. &amp; Hyde, K. D. (2020) Microfungi associated with Clematis (Ranunculaceae) with an integrated approach to delimiting species boundaries. Fungal Diversity 102: 1 - 203. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 13225 - 020 - 00448 - 4" type="journal article" year="2020">
Phukhamsakda 
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF7AF55A5F862B5FE77FE69" box="[456,512,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="236">et al.</emphasis>
(2020)
</bibRefCitation>
reported the new host record of 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF7AF55A7F262B5F8F1FE69" box="[962,1158,410,436]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pseudoberkleasmiaceae" genus="Pseudoberkleasmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="4" pageNumber="236" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="chiangmaiense">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF7AF55A7F262B5F8F1FE69" box="[962,1158,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="236">P. chiangmaiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF7AF55A0FB62B4F9D3FE69" box="[1227,1444,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Clematis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="4" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fulvicoma">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF7AF55A0FB62B4F9D3FE69" box="[1227,1444,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="236">Clematis fulvicoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while, 
<bibRefCitation id="595B24B5FFF7AF55A4E66291FDEDFE05" author="Bao, D. F. &amp; Hyde, K. D. &amp; McKenzie, E. H. &amp; Jeewon, R. &amp; Su, H. Y. &amp; Nalumpang, S. &amp; Luo, Z. L." box="[214,410,446,473]" pageId="4" pageNumber="236" pagination="669" refId="ref5218" refString="Bao, D. F., Hyde, K. D., McKenzie, E. H., Jeewon, R., Su, H. Y., Nalumpang, S. &amp; Luo, Z. L. (2021) Biodiversity of lignicolous freshwater hyphomycetes from China and Thailand and description of sixteen species. Journal of Fungi 7: 669. https: // doi. org / 10.3390 / jof 7080669" type="journal article" year="2021">
Bao 
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF7AF55A53C6291FD30FE05" box="[268,327,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="236">et al.</emphasis>
(2021)
</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF7AF55A6396291FEB8FE05" box="[521,719,446,472]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pseudoberkleasmiaceae" genus="Pseudoberkleasmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="4" pageNumber="236" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="chiangmaiense">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF7AF55A6396291FEB8FE05" box="[521,719,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="236">P. chiangmaiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from freshwater in 
<collectingCountry id="45DD19D4FFF7AF55A7856290FF8BFE05" box="[949,1020,446,472]" name="China" pageId="4" pageNumber="236">China</collectingCountry>
. Our collection was on 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF7AF55A13D6291F90DFE05" box="[1293,1402,447,472]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Zea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="4" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mays">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF7AF55A13D6291F90DFE05" box="[1293,1402,447,472]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="236">Zea mays</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and herein we provide the first host record of 
<taxonomicName id="FACA22C7FFF7AF55A66962CDFF6AFE21" box="[601,797,482,508]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pseudoberkleasmiaceae" genus="Pseudoberkleasmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="4" pageNumber="236" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="chiangmaiense">
<emphasis id="0FBE8556FFF7AF55A66962CDFF6AFE21" box="[601,797,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="236">P. chiangmaiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Maize.
</paragraph>
